  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to determine if emergency physician performed ultrasound-assisted
      lumbar puncture improves first-time success rates in a pediatric population. This will be
      done by comparison with current landmark-based approach to the procedure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
